data.content:
verb
-plies; -plied; -plying
[no obj] :to increase greatly in number or amount :to become much more numerous
Complaints about the new procedure soon multiplied.
Her responsibilities multiplied when she was promoted.
[+ obj] :to cause (something) to increase greatly in number or amount
Her responsibilities were multiplied by the promotion.
[no obj] :to increase in number by reproducing
The bacteria multiply rapidly in warm, moist conditions.
mathematics :to add a number to itself a certain number of times [+ obj]
If you multiply 5 by 2 you get 10. = If you multiply 5 and 2 (together) you get 10. = 5 multiplied by 2 equals 10. [no obj]
The teacher taught the children how to add, subtract, multiply, and divide. - compare divide

Động từ
nhân
children learning to multiply and divide
trẻ em học nhân và chia
and 2 multiply to makes
nhân 3 bằng
tăng thêm (về số lượng)
buy lot of raffles tickets and multiply your chance of success
mua nhiều vé số để tăng cơ may trúng số
sinh sản, nhân giống
rabbits multiply bacteria in the laboratory
có thể nhân giống vi khuẩn trong phòng thí nghiệm
